            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ],
          "text": "مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ الْحُسَيْنِ عَنْ جَعْفَرِ بْنِ مَحْبُوبٍ عَمَّنْ ذَكَرَهُ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) قَالَ"
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:12:1",
        "text": [
          " كُلُّ عَبْدٍ مُثِّلَ بِهِ فَهُوَ حُرٌّ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn, from Ja’far Bin Mahboub, from the one who mentioned it, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Every slave who is tortured with, so he is free’."
          ]
        }
